						               													<description>Terxo is an abstract alignment game, the more innovative tic tac toe evolution.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;(1)build a 3x3x3 cube: at the end, the player who score more points is the winner of the match!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each dice is different from the others, everyone have a specific Dice-Color, an impressed Sign, and Sign-Color)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;(2)You score a point when 3 pieces are sharing one characteristic in common (same dice color, same sign, or same color of the sign)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;(3)Aligments Are allowed in every linear direction throw the cube&amp;#10;&amp;#10;(4)You can score more than one point at the same time, for example, if you score in more than one direction or two characteristics on the same direction.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players doesn't have specific pieces, but the avaible pieces and the building cube are for all.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;(5)at each turn you receive the piece you have to play from the previous player.&amp;#10;After positioning your piece and declared how many points you score, you have to chose from the avaible dices the next dice you want to give to the next player!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;(6) each piece has to be placed in contact with pieces already placed (contact by placed above, on the side or by corner).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This way you never know, from the start, in which direction the cube will develop.&amp;#10; (7) Do not position pieces over the third dimension (by sides or hight)&amp;hellip; The final shape must still be a cube.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;(8) Pieces can not to be moved after being placed.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;(9)   2 players - Pl.1 VS Pl.2&amp;#10;      3 players - Pl.1 VS Pl.2 VS Pl.3 &amp;#10;      4 players - (Pl.1 &amp;amp; Pl.3) VS (Pl.1 &amp;amp; Pl.3)&amp;#10;(in 4, players plays in two teams with alternated players)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Terxo, This Board Less Board Game is a complete information game with high strategy and easy rules&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
